description: Neolacta, a Bengaluru-based company, continues to sell human milk despite licence cancellation. Interim stay by Karnataka high court and inaction of govt agencies allow this. India is the only country in Asia where breast milk is sold for profit.
title: Govt inaction lets firm sell human milk using HC stay

description: Finance minister Nirmala Sitharaman said the Modi govt intends to move on the reforms path to boost macroeconomic stability and growth, amid indications that the Union Budget will be presented around the third week of July, with consultations set to kick off over the next few days. After taking charge as finance minister for a second term, Sitharaman said the govt is fully committed to ensuring 'Ease of Living' for its citizens and will continue to take more steps.
title: Will pursue reforms to push growth, macro stability: FM

description: NCP (SCP) chief Sharad Pawar sought on Wednesday four to six months to effect a change in the Maharashtra govt, reports Anurag Bende. The veteran leader is on a three-day tour of Baramati to review the drought situation in the tehsil. He was visiting a village on Wednesday where he told people that MVA wants to win the assembly election, which may be held in Oct. Pawar criticised the Mahayuti govt, blaming it for not providing help to people, especially farmers facing an acute water crisis.
title: Need 4-6 mths to change Maha govt: Pawar in Baramati
Sena UBT, Congress give up a seat for each other for MLC polls
Art 21 lets adults go with anyone, says HC, quashes kidnapping FIR

description: In the city of Ahmedabad, temperatures climbed above 43C (109F) every day between May 19 and May 25, creating deadly hot working conditions for many of the labourers who keep the local economy humming. For 40-year-old Lataben Arvindbhai Makwana, it was unbearable to run her sewing machine inside her tin-roofed house, which has little ventilation and only a small ceiling fan.
title: How insurance cover helped 46k women avoid toiling in sun during heatwave

description: After two days of searches in Kochi on a multi-level marketing company, Enforcement Directorate on Wednesday attached bank deposits of Rs 32 crore, taking the total attachment in the case so far to Rs 260 crore. The directors of the company are accused of collecting over Rs 1,500 crore from the public and laundering the 'proceeds of crime'.
title: ED attaches 32 crore bank deposits of ponzi co

description: Denying any question paper leak, National Testing Agency (NTA) is likely to oppose any move for cancellation of NEET-UG 2024. There are multiple petitions being filed in high courts and SC on diverse allegations - right from question paper leaks to grace marks and significant jump in the number of high scorers.
title: Sanctity of NEET-UG exam not compromised, says NTA

description: NHAI orders changes at toll plazas to improve FASTag transactions by mandating STQC-certified equipment for RFID reader and antenna to prevent glitches and ensure hassle-free commuting.
title: New devices to check FASTag to cut toll plaza delays soon: NHAI

description: Government plans to import 11 lakh tonne of chana from Australia to address rising pulse prices, in addition to 16 lakh tonne of yellow peas used as a substitute after removing import duty.
title: Govt plans to import additional chana from Australia to check prices

description: Former Karnataka CM BS Yediyurappa summoned by CID for questioning related to a Pocso case. Allegations include sexual harassment under IPC Section 354-A.
title: CID asks Karnataka ex-CM BSY to face probe team in Pocso case

description: India ranked 129 out of 146 countries in the Global Gender Gap Report 2024 by World Economic Forum, closing 64.1% of its gender gap with a slight decrease in score compared to the previous year.
title: India slips 2 notches to 129 in WEF global gender gap index

description: Bombay HC upheld the landowner's right to redevelopment, striking down SRA's proposed acquisition of Mount Mary Church land. Bishop John Rodrigues petitioned against the acquisition.
title: HC junks Maha govt bid to take over church land
3 dead as bus falls into Uttarakhand gorge

description: An article in the latest edition of the RSS mouthpiece, Organiser, has described the admission of Ajit Pawar-led Nationalist Congress Party (NCP) into the BJP-Shiv Sena govt as an ill-advised step, which "hurt" BJP's cadre. The criticism has come days after RSS chief Mohan Bhagwat's comment about the lack of political decorum in the Lok Sabha campaign.
title: Ajit's NCP slams RSS mag for questioning its entry into NDA

description: A special trial court granted permission to question Abu Jundal about an absconding accused. In 2016, Jundal was convicted in the Aurangabad arms haul case and is suspected to have been a handler of the 10 Pakistani terrorists involved in the attacks.
title: 26/11 accused to be quizzed to track down ‘absconder’

description: Actor Salman Khan, who has been allegedly facing persistent threats from the Lawrence Bishnoi gang, while recording his statement before the crime branch expressed his frustration and exhaustion over being targeted for a crime he claims to have already suffered greatly from and paid fines imposed by various courts.
title: Exhausted over being targeted: Salman Khan to cops

description: A four-wheeler ferrying cattle in Seraikela-Kharsawan district in Jharkhand was set on fire by unidentified persons early on Wednesday. Nine bovines were recovered from the vehicle, police said. The incident occurred at Ganjiya barrage near Udaipur village under the Gamharia police station in Kharsawan. Locals informed the police that they saw some individuals repairing a vehicle early morning.
title: Vehicle ferrying cattle set ablaze in Jharkhand, probe launched
Five on two bikes crushed between truck and bus in Tamil Nadu

description: Retail inflation eased to a 12-month low in May. NSO data showed CPI at 4.8%. IIP growth held at 5%. Rajani Sinha expects RBI to cut rates by 50 basis points in FY25.
title: Retail inflation at 12-mth low, IIP holds steady at 5%

description: Former BrahMos scientist Nishant Agrawal, who was sentenced to life by a sessions court here on June 3 for leaking military secrets to Pakistan, worked in the missile assembly unit at Nagpur and was involved in delivery of close to 80 missiles to the armed forces during his four-year stint. He had access to customers and delivery locations of missiles, as per Major General (retd) Achyut Deo, general manager, BrahMos Aerospace Private Limited (BAPL), who deposed as a witness during Nishant's trial.
title: Jailed BrahMos scientist delivered 80 missiles to forces

description: PM Narendra Modi and Canadian PM Trudeau to meet at G7 summit in Italy. India reiterated its concerns over Canada's support for anti-India elements. The PM will participate in the G7 outreach session on Friday and is also expected to have many bilateral meetings with G7 and other invitee leaders.
title: PM Modi to face Trudeau at G7, may take up separatist issue

description: Samajwadi Party national president Akhilesh Yadav formally resigned from Karhal assembly seat to retain Kannauj Lok Sabha constituency, on Wednesday. Newly elected MP from Ayodhya, Awadhesh Prasad, who is a sitting MLA from Milkipur, has also forwarded his resignation to the Speaker.
title: MP Akhilesh Yadav quits Karhal assembly seat
Taking 'break' for medical reasons: TMC's Abhishek

description: As the National Democratic Alliance (NDA) govts were installed in two more states with Chandrababu Naidu and Mohan Charan Majhi taking oaths as chief ministers in Andhra Pradesh and Odisha respectively, Prime Minister Narendra Modi on Wednesday expressed confidence that the new govts will usher in record development in both the states.
title: Andhra, Odisha will usher in record development: PM Modi

description: BJP formalised Pema Khandu as the Arunachal Pradesh's 18th CM after leading the party to an electoral landslide. Khandu, the youngest CM at 44, thanked PM Modi and Nadda for support. This was BJP's second consecutive electoral landslide in the state with 46 seats — 10 of them unopposed — to build on its 2019 tally of 41 and leave Congress clinging to a solitary seat in its erstwhile stronghold of over three decades.
title: Khandu set for 5th term as BJP finalises him as Arunachal CM

description: Several individuals were wounded by gunfire on Wednesday in a neighborhood situated in the northern part of Illinois, according to officials. The Lost Lake community near Dixon saw a significant law enforcement presence, along with ambulances and two medical helicopters, as reported on the Winnebago Boone & Ogle County Fire/Ems Incidents Facebook page.
title: Multiple people shot in northern Illinois community, authorities say

description: President Droupadi Murmu rejects mercy petition of Pakistani terrorist Mohd Arif in Red Fort attack case, where he killed 3 jawans in 2000.
title: Red Fort attack: President rejects mercy plea of Pakistani man

description: Odisha saw the swearing-in of Mohan Charan Majhi as the first BJP CM, ending Naveen Patnaik's 24-year rule. PM Modi and Naveen were present at the event.
title: With Patnaik on dais, Majhi is sworn in, inducts 15 in cabinet

description: N Chandrababu Naidu made a spectacular comeback in Vijayawada to take oath as Andhra Pradesh's CM for the fourth time. He took the oath on Wednesday along with 21 ministers of TDP, and one member from BJP. Actor and Jana Sena Party (JSP) chief Pawan Kalyan, who was instrumental in forging the winning combination with TDP and BJP, joined the cabinet and is tipped to get the deputy CM's post.
title: 21 of 24 mins from TDP, Kalyan likely to be deputy CM

description: A video showing a brief interaction between home minister Amit Shah and former Telangana governor Tamilisai Soundararajan went viral Wednesday. In the video, Shah is seen wagging his finger while speaking to Tamilisai in the presence of former veep Venkaiah Naidu and Union ministers J P Nadda and Nitin Gadkari.
title: Video showing Shah wagging finger at TN BJP neta goes viral

description: A 16-year-old boy fell into an open pump chamber of Ambazari dam and died around 4am on Tuesday. After celebrating his birthday with his family at midnight, he had sneaked out around 3am and gone to a friend's house. The friend told police that after walking around Jaripatka for 15-20 minutes, they had decided to go to Shankar Nagar Square to have poha. However, they found that the poha stall was yet to open and went to Ambazari lake and played PubG there.
title: Boy cuts b'day cake, then sneaks out and plays PubG; ends up dead

description: A man and his son, both lawyers, were shot dead by miscreants while they were on way to Chapra court in Bihar's Saran, Wednesday. Police have arrested two accused. The deceased were identified as Ram Ayodhya Prasad Yadav (70) and his son Sunil Kumar Yadav (30), residents of Methwalia village. Both were rushed to Chapra Sadar Hospital, where they were declared dead on arrival.
title: Man and son, both lawyers, shot on way to court

description: A fire incident in Kuwait claimed the lives of over 40 Indian foreign workers. PM Modi announced relief for the deceased families and sent a representative to assist with repatriation and support for the injured.
title: Over 40 Indians among 49 dead in Kuwait blaze

description: Congress MP Rahul Gandhi, who won in Wayanad and Rae Bareli Lok Sabha constituencies, said during his Wayanad visit that he was in a dilemma over which of the two he should represent in Parliament. "Everybody knows the answer except me. In politics, everybody knows everything except the person who is doing it," he said.
title: Wayanad or Rae Bareli, which to quit? My call will make people at both seats happy: Rahul

description: A six-member gang from Delhi and a pub organiser (person who leases a pub) from Hyderabad involved in a dating racket were arrested in Nagpur on Wednesday. They were brought here and produced before a court, which remanded them in judicial custody. The suspects targeted youngsters on dating apps, luring them with rendezvous with young women at a pub in Madhapur area of the city, where they would be forced to buy expensive liquor and food.
title: 6 of Delhi gang, pub manager in Hyd held for dating scam

description: A third-year resident doctor in the orthopaedic department of Surat Municipal Institute of Medical Education and Research (SMIMER) was suspended Wednesday for allegedly assaulting a Thai woman in the boys' hostel. Rutvik Darji will remain suspended pending inquiry by dean Deepak Hovale.
title: Surat civic hospital doctor assaults Thai woman in boys' hostel

description: Eight family members from the Nat nomadic community were killed when a sand-laden truck overturned on their hut in Hardoi district, UP. The bodies were retrieved using earth movers.
title: Sand-laden truck overturns on hut in UP, 8 of a family killed

description: The first session of Parliament after the Lok Sabha polls will be held from June 24 to July 3. President Droupadi Murmu will address a joint sitting on June 27. The opposition plans to raise issues like the recent NEET controversy.
title: 1st post-poll Parliament session from June 24, likely to be storm

description: Pakistan's new Shehbaz Sharif-led government presented its first federal budget of 18.5 trillion rupees amid talks with the IMF for a bailout, crucial for averting an economic default.
title: IMF bailout terms hang heavy over Pak govt’s first federal budget

description: A CRPF constable from Madhya Pradesh and two suspected Pakistani terrorists were killed in a 15-hour overnight operation that began late Tuesday in the frontier village of Seda Sohal in Kathua district of Jammu division, where an intelligence alert about a likely fidayeen strike was sounded Wednesday.
title: J&K police releases sketches of terrorists involved in Doda strike

description: Skipper Rohit Sharma on Wednesday acknowledged the fact that Team India struggled in a below-par chase of 111 despite defeating United States by seven wickets in a T20 World Cup Group A game in New York. With their third win in a row, India qualified for the Super Eight stage riding on a fighting fifty by Suryakumar Yadav and Arshdeep Singh's four-wicket haul.
title: 'Could've been anyone's game', admits Rohit Sharma

description: India overcame early setbacks to defeat the 'giant killers' USA, becoming the third team to qualify for the Super Eight stage after Australia and South Africa. With this seven-wicket victory, India remained unbeaten, securing their third consecutive win in Group A after defeating Ireland and Pakistan.
title: 5 penalty runs! Rookie mistake from USA

description: Suryakumar Yadav hit an unbeaten half-century and left-arm seamer Arshdeep Singh claimed a career-best 4-9 as India defeated the United States by seven wickets to reach the T20 World Cup second round on Wednesday. Chasing 111 to win the Group A clash, India were rattled at 15-2 and then 44-3 before Yadav (50) and Shivam Dube (31) put on an undefeated fourth-wicket stand of 67 to secure a third win in three games for Rohit Sharma's team with 10 balls to spare.
title: T20 WC: Suryakumar Yadav, Arshdeep Singh shine as India beat USA to reach Super 8s

description: A fire in a Kuwait labor housing facility claimed 40 Indian lives and injured over 50. The Ministry of External Affairs expressed condolences and is seeking details. The Indian Embassy is assisting the injured and coordinating with Kuwaiti authorities.
title: Tragic fire in Kuwait claims over 40 Indian lives

description: Chasing 111 to win the Group A clash, India were rattled at 15 for 2 and then 42 for 3 before Suryakumar Yadav (50*) and Shivam Dube (31*) put on an undefeated fourth-wicket stand of 67 to secure a third win in 3 games for Rohit Sharma's team with 10 balls to spare.
title: How USA gave India a run for their money
Why top economist thinks US market is heading for a mega crash

description: Odisha's BJP government in its first cabinet meeting approved a proposal to re-open all four gates of Shree Jagannath Temple in Puri on early Thursday morning and set up a corpus fund for immediate requirement of the 12th-century shrine. This was stated by Chief Minister Mohan Charan Majhi after chairing a meeting with his ministers at the state secretariat Lok Seva Bhawan.
title: Big decision in 1st sitting of new Odisha cabinet
PM Modi at G7 Summit: What is on the agenda

description: The Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) has put forward a proposal for the ICC Champions Trophy 2025 to commence on February 19 and be hosted entirely in Pakistan. The PCB has firmly rejected the idea of a hybrid model for India's matches, similar to the arrangement made for the Asia Cup 2023. According to the PCB's proposed schedule, the ICC Champions Trophy 2025 will span from February 19 to March 9, 2025, with all matches taking place in three major Pakistani cities: Karachi, Rawalpindi, and Lahore.
title: CT: PCB rejects hybrid model for India’s matches

description: Virat Kohli has had a horrendous show so far at the T20 World Cup in the Americas, scoring -- 1, 4 and 0 in three outings. After dismissing Kohli in the third-ball of the game, Saurabh Netravalkar went on to dismiss India skipper Rohit Sharma in his second over to leave India in early trouble in chase of 111.
title: Netravalkar 'engineers' Kohli's golden duck
Encounter under way in J&K's Doda district, 1 cop hurt; 4th terror incident in 3 days

description: Apple surpasses Microsoft to become the world's most valuable company after announcing AI features at WWDC.
title: Apple beats Microsoft, becomes world’s most valuable company

description: Left-arm Indian seamer Arshdeep Singh made an immediate impact when he opened the bowling against the USA in the Group A encounter. His first delivery resulted in the dismissal of USA opener Shayan Jahangir, who was adjudged leg before wicket, for duck. The young Indian seamer continued his impressive spell by claiming another wicket in the same over, removing Andries Gous (2). USA managed to score just 18 runs for the loss of two wickets in the first six overs. This was also the USA's lowest powerplay total in T20Is.
title: USA register unwanted record vs India in T20 World Cup

description: A family in Kerala's Kollam district is praying that the news they received unofficially on Wednesday morning about the tragedy that struck Shameer, their sole breadwinner, in the Kuwait fire incident, is not true. Shameer, hailing from Vayyankara village in this south Kerala district, had been working in Kuwait for the past few years. It was at around 11.30 am that his family received information from a friend about the reported tragic death of Shemeer in the fire.
title: Family in Kerala awaits confirmation on breadwinner's fate in Kuwait fire

description: With the early strike, Arshdeep created history, becoming the first India bowler to grab a wicket first-ball in a T20 World Cup game. The 25-year-old then went on to pick up his second wicket in the same over, dismissing Andries Gous for 2 on the final ball. Earlier, India captain Rohit Sharma won the toss and opted to bowl first against co-hosts United States in their third Group A game.
title: Arshdeep's celebrappeal leaves internet buzzing. Watch

description: The pope has again used a highly disparaging word against gay people for which he had already apologised last month, ANSA news agency said on Tuesday. Italian media had attributed to the pope the use of the word "frociaggine", a vulgar Italian term roughly translating as "faggotness", on May 20 during a closed-door meeting with Italian bishops.
title: Pope Francis under fire again for using homophobic slur

description: Arshdeep Singh made history in the T20 World Cup by taking a wicket on the first delivery, a feat no Indian bowler had achieved before.
title: Arshdeep first India bowler in T20 WC history to...

description: Apple has surpassed Microsoft to become the world's most valuable company with a market value of $3.25 trillion. The tech giant's advancements in artificial intelligence, including new AI-enhanced features and software improvements, have fueled this rise.
title: Apple reclaims world’s most valuable firm title; dethrones Microsoft

description: The United States team got a major blow on Wednesday as their regular skipper Monank Patel has been ruled out due to shoulder injury just before the start of the crucial T20 World Cup clash against India in New York. Star batter Aaron Jones replaced Patel as captain for this game. The severity of the injury is not known yet and one can hope that Patel might recover for USA's last Group game against Ireland on Friday.
title: T20 WC: USA skipper Monank ruled out of India clash due to injury

description: Apart from mega events such as the Olympics, the FIFA World Cup, and the Cricket World Cup, the IPL is the only property in the world that has the ability to reach over a billion-plus populace, with its popularity not just limited to the Indian subcontinent, the report said.
title: IPL valuation rises to $16.4 billion in 2024: Report

description: Elon Musk, CEO of Tesla and SpaceX, accused of sexual relationships with employees. WSJ report reveals uncomfortable work culture created by Musk at Tesla and SpaceX.

description: Stay updated with the latest in entertainment! Highlights include Kevin Jonas’s skin cancer diagnosis, Kartik Aaryan confirming his single status, and Ananya Panday’s lip filler speculations. Alia Bhatt starts prepping for 'Love and War,' and Kangana Ranaut visits Sadhguru after becoming a Member of Parliament.

description: Netravalkar is living both the American dream (becoming a professionally successful migrant in the Shining City on the Top of the Hill) and the Indian dream (beating Pakistan in a crunch match) at the same time. Next up he faces off against the nation he represented as a youngster, against team members with whom he has shared the dressing room.
title: T20 World Cup: Saurabh Netravalkar wants to spoil India's applecart in the Big Apple

title: Ashwin daughter's 'too complicated' query

description: The bigwigs of politics and Tollywood gathered in Vijayawada on Wednesday to witness oath ceremony of new Andhra Pradesh chief minister Chandrababu Naidu. But now that it's down, a video clip of an interaction between Union home minister Amit Shah and former Telangana governor Tamilisai Soundararajan has sparked speculation about potential rifts within the BJP's state unit.
title: Amid Annamalai vs Tamilisai, video of 'chastising' Shah goes viral

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi will visit Apulia, Italy, on the invitation of Italian PM Giorgia Meloni to attend the 50th G7 Summit on June 14, marking his first overseas trip since starting his third term, announced Foreign Secretary Vinay Mohan Kwatra. This visit will allow Modi to engage with global leaders on issues significant to India and the Global South, following up on last year's G20 summit outcomes.
title: PM Modi to travel to Italy in first foreign visit of third term
Pawan Kalyan's wealth: A glimpse into financial standing of AP's dy CM

description: India's primary market is poised for a surge of IPOs with over two dozen companies planning to raise more than Rs 30,000 crore in the next two months. Investor confidence is high post Modi government's return, signaling stable governance and policies.
title: Over 2 dozen offerings lined up to raise Rs 30,000 cr over next 2 months

description: Pawan Kalyan and Chiranjeevi posed with Prime Minister Narendra Modi at the swearing-in event in one of the many viral moments from the ceremony.

description: UK economy stagnates in April before elections. Labour Party criticises PM Rishi Sunak. Economist Paul Dales comments on GDP impact. Britain rebounded from recession earlier this year with growth in first quarter. Economy faced mild contraction due to heightened inflation.
title: Zero growth: UK economy slows to halt in April ahead of general elections

description: The 2009 champions faced a shocking defeat to USA in their opening match, which they lost in 'Super Over' tiebreaker. It followed a defeat against traditional rivals India after being in the winning position for 32 of the 40 overs in the match. As a result, the team's hopes of progressing to the 'Super 8' stage are not anymore in their hands alone now.
title: 'Calling Babar Azam king is like a click-bait YouTube thumbnail'

description: Apple just dropped the latest update for iPhones, iOS 18. It is the biggest overhaul in the years, so big that you’ll now be able to customise your Home Screen with colours, and place icons anywhere on it. Control Center has also been overhauled – the first change since iOS 11. Not only that but the Photos app also has a new look, there are a couple of new tricks in Messages, too. It doesn’t stop here, there are plenty of new features. So, here’s a quick rundown of the biggest new features that’ll come to your iPhone later this year.
title: 10 biggest new features coming to your iPhones later this year

description: Rahul Gandhi questioned PM Narendra Modi's silence on Wednesday on two different terror attacks that occurred in Jammu and Kashmir over the course of the previous three days. He claimed that the nation demanded an explanation for why, during the BJP administration, the terrorists had escaped capture.
title: Rahul questions PM Modi's silence over J&K terror attacks

description: Akhilesh Yadav resigns as Karhal MLA and Leader of the Opposition in UP Assembly. He reclaimed the Yadav family bastion of Kannauj by winning the LS seat. Awadhesh Prasad resigns from his MLA position after winning from Faizabad LS constituency.
title: SP's Akhilesh Yadav, Ayodhya MP Awadhesh Prasad resign from UP assembly

title: 'Talk with neighbours only option': Farooq after terror attacks

description: The IPL has transformed cricket into a lucrative business, says former Pakistani all-rounder Shahid Afridi. He highlights how the IPL has spurred the creation of numerous other leagues worldwide, showcasing the financial potential of white-ball cricket. Afridi notes that this commercialization has opened opportunities for many players, offering financial stability and new avenues for showcasing talent.
title: 'Cricket ek business ban gaya hai...': Shahid Afridi

title: Sensex at 1 lakh? Markets jumped 93% during FM’s first stint

description: The stage was set and emotions ran high as Telugu Desam Party chief N Chandrababu Naidu prepared to take oath as the new chief minister of Andhra Pradesh. This grand comeback is nothing short of a masala film script and to witness it were present celebrities like celebrities like Rajinikanth, Chiranjeevi, Ram Charan and more. The TDP played a crucial role in the NDA government formation this time, and to support the party chief on his big day on stage was Prime Minister Narendra Modi.
title: Watch: Emotional Naidu gets long hug, pat on back from PM Modi

description: Pakistan's donkey population was 5.5 million in 2019-2020, 5.6 million in 2020-21, 5.7 million in 2021-22, and 5.8 million in 2022-23, 5.9 million in 2023-24 recording a steady rise.
title: Pakistan's donkey population increases but country misses GDP growth

description: India faces USA in a T20 World Cup match at Nassau County International Cricket Stadium. US cricketers discuss taking on India, including facing Rohit Sharma. With two victories in as many games, the USA squad has been dominating the T20 World Cup. The Indian team, which the US team has never played in any format, is packed with IPL superstars.
title: 'You play fire with fire…': Ali Khan on playing against Virat Kohli

description: After being shocked by co-hosts USA with a 'Super Over' defeat in their tournament opener, Pakistan let a win against India slip out of hands, which led to a national outcry against skipper Babar Azam and his team. Pakistan's 'Super 8' qualification is in troubled waters, dependent on other results in the group and a win against Ireland in their last group match.
title: 'Mulq ke jazbaat ka satyanaash maar diya': Akram lambasts Pak team

description: The Supreme Court criticized the Delhi government for failing to address the water crisis and warned of involving Delhi Police to tackle the tanker mafia. The government's actions to control water wastage during recurring water scarcity were questioned, highlighting the people's suffering shown in media reports.
title: What action have you taken against 'tanker mafia': SC to Delhi govt

description: At least 15 museums in Delhi, including the Railway Museum, received hoax bomb threats on Tuesday. Following these threats, the Delhi Police registered a case and launched an investigation. In a separate incident on Tuesday, a 13-year-old boy was taken into custody for allegedly sending a bomb threat email. The email targeted a flight scheduled from Delhi to Toronto on June 4.
title: Over 10 Delhi museums get bomb threats
The 'aandhi' power: Meet Andhra minister Pawan Kalyan

description: Harbhajan Singh has criticized Pakistan cricketer Kamran Akmal for his 'racist' comment about India pacer Arshdeep Singh during the India-Pakistan clash in New York. Singh acknowledged Akmal's apology but warned against repeating such transgressions. He described the statement as absurd and childish, urging Akmal to understand that there is no need to mock anyone's religion.
title: Harbhajan denounces Kamran as 'nalaayak' for 'racist' remark

description: NHAI invites global EOIs to develop a GNSS-based electronic toll collection system in India to integrate it within the existing FASTag framework. The system uses RFID technology for automatic toll deduction, eliminating the need for cash lanes, and supports both pre-paid accounts and post-paid billing.
title: How upcoming Satellite-based Toll system different from FASTag

description: Joe Biden hugged his son Hunter after the verdict was out on Tuesday. But it's unlikely that the US president would extend presidential pardon to his son.

description: Eight members of a family died in Hardoi after a sand-laden truck overturned on their hut. The police, with the help of local residents, managed to upright the truck and remove the sand.
title: 8 of a family dead after truck overturns on their hut in UP

description: Chinese Premier Li Qiang extended his congratulations to Prime Minister Narendra Modi for securing a historic third consecutive term, following PM Modi's recent oath-taking ceremony at Rashtrapati Bhavan. Chinese ambassador to India, Xu Feihong, shared this update on X. Xu highlighted that Premier Li expressed a willingness to collaborate with India to advance the bilateral relations between the two nations in a positive direction.
title: Chinese Premier Li Qiang congratulates PM Modi on his historic 3rd term

description: Pune police, Army forensic expert, and crash impact analysis report investigate the Porsche car accident involving two IT professionals in Pune. The report aims to establish a connection between the car's impact and the victims' injuries.
title: Pune Porsche crash: Police prepare crash impact analysis report

description: A victory for India will mean that the former champions will advance to the next stage, where they will join South Africa and Australia -- the two teams so far to have made it to the 'Super 8s'. That result will also breathe new life into Pakistan's campaign that stayed alive after their win over Canada.
title: T20 WC: What happens to Group A if USA upset India

description: 28 out of 71 ministers in PM Narendra Modi's cabinet have criminal cases, including serious charges like murders and crimes against women. BJP ministers Shantanu Thakur and Sukanta Majumdar from West Bengal have murder charges against them. Suresh Gopi, Bandi Sanjay Kumar, and Jual Oram also face criminal charges. Additionally, Amit Shah and Giriraj Singh have cases of hate speech.
title: Modi cabinet 3.0: 39% ministers have criminal cases against them

description: Pakistan's Mohammad Rizwan has equalled India captain Rohit Sharma's record of most half-centuries as an opener in T20 internationals, achieving this during Pakistan's seven-wicket victory over Canada in the T20 World Cup. Both Rizwan and Sharma have amassed 30 fifties as openers in the dynamic 20-over format.
title: Mohammad Rizwan equals Rohit Sharma's big T20I record

description: Parliamentary affairs minister Kiren Rijiju announced on Wednesday that the 18th Lok Sabha's first session will commence on June 24. The election of the Lok Sabha Speaker will follow the start of the parliamentary session. There is a noteworthy negotiation taking place between the Bharatiya Janata Party and its NDA allies. Typically, the Speaker is chosen during the inaugural meeting of Lok Sabha members.
title: First session of 18th Lok Sabha to begin on June 24

description: In a controversial FIFA World Cup Qualifier, India took an early lead against Qatar with Lallianzuala Chhangte's goal. The match turned when Qatar's Yousef Aymen scored amid protests that the ball had gone out. Despite Indian objections, the goal stood, and Qatar secured a 2-1 victory, impacting India's qualifying chances.
title: Watch: Controversial Qatar goal puts India out of FIFA qualifiers

description: Stock market today: Indian equity benchmark indices, BSE Sensex and Nifty50, opened in green on Wednesday. While BSE Sensex moved up above 76,600, Nifty50 was near 23,300.
title: Sensex up over 150 points near 76,600 level; Nifty50 above 23,300

description: Apple rebrands Apple ID to 'Apple Account' for a consistent sign-in experience across its ecosystem with the rollout of iOS 18, macOS Sequoia, and watchOS 11.
title: Apple makes Apple ID your Apple account: Details

description: Johnson & Johnson has agreed to pay a $700 million settlement to resolve a probe by 42 US states and Washington, DC. The inquiry examined the marketing of their baby powder and other talc-based products, which have faced allegations of causing cancer. The settlement addresses claims that Johnson & Johnson deceived consumers about the safety of its talc products.
title: Johnson & Johnson reaches $700m talc settlement with US govt

description: Australia secured their Super Eights berth in the T20 World Cup with a nine-wicket victory over Namibia in Antigua. Adam Zampa's four wickets for 12 runs in four overs helped Australia reach the Super Eight stage. Namibia's batting lineup was reduced to 72 runs in 17 overs, marking the lowest total Australia have ever restricted an opponent.
title: Zampa's record-setting spell propels Australia into Super Eights

description: In Buenos Aires on Tuesday, a Polish daredevil was arrested while attempting to scale a 30-story building without the aid of ropes. Marcin Banot, wearing an Argentine football jersey, was intercepted by onlookers after climbing 25 floors of the Globant building. More than 30 firefighters, ambulances, and police cars arrived on the scene after an emergency call was made by someone inside the building.
title: Polish 'Spider-Man' arrested for trying to climb 30-storey building without ropes

description: The government on Tuesday announced that Lt Gen Upendra Dwivedi will be the next chief of the Army Staff succeeding incumbent Gen Manoj Pande. Dwivedi is presently serving as the Vice Chief of the Army Staff. The tenure of the present Chief of the Army Staff, General Manoj C Pande, ends on June 30.
title: All you need to know about Lt Gen Upendra Dwivedi

description: WHO confirms second human case of avian influenza A(H9N2) in India, a 4-year-old from West Bengal state in 2019, recovered and discharged. Infection likely due to poultry exposure; H9N2 is a less pathogenic strain with potential to reassort with other viruses, rare human cases reported.
title: 4-yr-old in India tests positive for H9N2 bird flu, 2nd in country

description: Tim Cook acknowledged the possibility of false information from 'Apple Intelligence' and highlighted time-saving benefits for customers.
title: 'Sort of calling … ': Tim Cook on calling AI system, Apple Intelligence

description: Three security personnel were injured during an exchange of fire between terrorists and security forces in the Doda district of Jammu and Kashmir after an attack on a joint checkpoint. Additionally, police and security forces are conducting an operation to apprehend a terrorist hiding in Seda Sohal village, Kathua district. This follows an attack near the International Border that resulted in one civilian being injured and a terrorist killed.
title: Third in 72 hours: Terrorists attack checkpost in J&K's Doda; 3 security personnel injured

description: Saurav Gupta, 21, died in a terror attack in Jammu's Reasi. His wife, Shivani Gupta, survived with injuries. They were on a pilgrimage to Vaishno Devi shrine.
title: Delhi man killed in terror attack in J&K's Reasi tried to warn others

description: India prepare to face USA in a crucial match. Jasprit Bumrah's pace poses a challenge for the hosts. USA's unexpected victory against Pakistan adds to the anticipation.
title: T20 World Cup: India eye Super Eight berth in clash against USA
Compensation of Rs 1.2k crore paid in Ayodhya: DM
‘India GitHub developers to pip US in 27’

description: USA's cricket dream attracted talent through $50k contracts, Major League Cricket, and local tournaments, raising the game's level despite lacking professional infrastructure. Professionalism is still a distant goal. The minor league is played in makeshift grounds which are mostly public parks. There is no concept of a coaching staff in those teams and playing XIs are largely picked by the promoters of the clubs.
title: T20 World Cup: The template which shaped USA's rise

description: Rupee weakens due to rising dollar index. US Fed policy crucial. Emkay Global report predicts short-term pressure on rupee due to dollar demand.
title: Rupee logs new record low of 83.57 vs dollar

description: India-born cricketer Saurabh Netravalkar will bowl against his country at the Twenty20 World Cup on Wednesday. The match will pit India's Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli against Netravalkar and Nosthush Kenjige. Despite being the tournament favorite, India will approach the match cautiously, having seen the U.S. defeat Pakistan in a stunning upset.
title: T20 WC: It's Netravalkar & Kenjige vs Rohit & Virat in New York

description: The Supreme Court, in a preliminary assessment, has determined that the integrity of the NEET-UG 2024 examination may have been compromised. On Tuesday, the court demanded clarification from the National Testing Agency (NTA) regarding alleged improprieties in the administration of the test, including accusations of paper leakage. The bench issued the order and resolved to scrutinize NEET 2024 after a concise hearing.
title: Sanctity of NEET-UG has been affected, we need answers: SC

description: Security forces in Jammu and Rajouri districts are on high alert following an ambush on a pilgrim bus in Reasi. The attackers, suspected to be LeT terrorists, are believed to have fled to escape the search operation.
title: Forces step up hunt for Reasi attackers, sketch of an ultra released
